      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PASS ME NOT (4) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Has finished in the money at the last three runs. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings six times from 11 starts. Likely to be in the finish again. DIVORCE PAPERS (1) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by one length at this track in a handy 16.66 beating Sweet Legs. Has definite claims. SWIFT ETHICS (2) had a tricky draw and ran well to finish second, beaten half a length, (16.83) at this track. Will give a great sight again. WHISKEY MY WAY (3) has been a model of consistency and deserves plenty of thought.",
